claim.claim-text:
1. A nonvolatile memory device comprising:
a plurality of word lines on a semiconductor substrate;
a ground select line at a side of the word lines;
a string select line at another side of the word lines;
a first dummy word line between the ground select line and a first word line, wherein the first word line is nearest to the ground select line among the word lines; and
a second dummy word line between the string select line and a second word line, wherein the second word line is nearest to the string select line among the word lines,
wherein each of a first distance between the ground select line and the first dummy word line and a second distance between the first dummy word line and the first word line is greater than a third distance between a pair of the word lines adjacent to each other.
